<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by IpkusTheGnome:
[B]I am not posting here to create upset. I do support the KGC. I believe now after seeing all of your replys that I should have titled my post "Request" instead of "complaint". I am now currently without a guild so I do not have an officer to ask about the current rotations. 

I do have a few questions though...

1. If a guild chooses to not be a part of the KGC and they wish to kill mobs on the KGC rotations what would the KGC's posistion on this be? 

2. If groups of players or a single player wishes to kill a KGC rotation mob how does one go about doing this. For example a necro can solo VS (http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx?path=/Yaguex/fullsize/Yag+VS.jpg) and single groups can kill many of the dragons (ie Zlandicar). So if a group sees one of these mobs spawn then and engages before any KGC guild or alliance is there and follows the standard Play nice policy, then KGC wont have a problem with this?

3. Assuming that you do have a problem with people that do not belong to your organization killing mobs that are on your rotations would that not go against everything the KGC stands for? It would in essence be as if the KGC is perma camping these mobs and not allowing anyone else a chance at them.

4. Kellroy, you mention that if I have a problem, issue, or suggestion that I need to bring it up on the main board for discussion. Well I would have been happy to post this on the main board but I do not have access to the main board. So does that mean you will grant me access to the main board if I were to ask for it?


The following is only in regards to Mkar's posts. 
First off I post on the karana boards which are there to post whatever anyone wants too. There is even a flame section which is in place allowing everyone to flame all they want. I usually post int he flame section just to rile things up and have fun with it. Imo most of the people that post on the karana boards are the more liberal players of the karana server.

Yes, I copied my post from here just to get a view of from everyone in karana. Since the KGC stands for karana guild council they are a major part of the karana server and should be available for discussion on a karana board. Now you didnt see me going to all of the individual guilds boards and posting there, because that would be very inappropriate of me. I am only posting here to discuss why the list of rotations isnt viewable by all. I could have simply created a psuedoname to post this with so that way none of you would know who I really am, but I dont want to hide my views. I dont think Karana would be where it is without the rotations. Just with the current abilites of players (level 65) and new equipment many of the mobs that used to require a raid force can be killed with a single group or less. There are also rumors of the next expansion raising the level cap to 70. If that is so then you may see mages soloing Klandicar or Trakanon.

Ipkus
61 Magician


P.S. As a side note I dont want to be givin a bad reputation because I was part of ACoP. I only raided with them a few times and was never a part of anything "bad" they may have done. The moment ACoP left the KGC I logged in and guildremoved myself. Please judge me on your own for the person and player that I am. If you ever need anything in game you can send me a tell and I will always be willing to help out, that is assuming I am not dead in CoD again, damn I swear I spend more time dead there than actually killin stuff. I havent posted here to whine, moan, or bitch about how KGC is this big bad organization, I am just looking for answers to my questions. And lastly I am a computer geek in rl not a writer so I may not always express myself in the most polite manner.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
